initECO(25.10)                                                  initECO(25.10)

Name
       initECO - Logs ECO operations in a log file

Syntax
       initECO

       [-help]

       <ecoFileName>

       Logs ECO operations in a log file.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each initECO parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man initECO.

       <ecoFileName>
              Specifies the name of the ECO log file.

Examples
              * The following commands show the usage of initECO and endECO..

                initECO <File1>....<ECO commands>....endECO

                All  operations  performed  by  ECO  Commands  are  logged  in
                <File1>.

Related Information
              * endECO

              * loadECO

